commit.message: Drop support for GHC 7, bytestring < 0.10.4 and text < 1.1.2
v0.4.2.3: fix "non-canoncial mappend" warnings, support bytestring-0.12 and text-2.1
Haskell-CI: include GHC 9.4.1 alpha, restrict to master
Fix #2: Make Monoid instances canonical with mappend = (<>)

Bump to 0.4.2.2; prepare release

- description in .cabal file copied from README
- formatting README
- new maintainer: community github.com/blaze-builder
- switch stability to `Stable`
Makefile: use GHC=ghc (but benchmarks need makeover)
Restructure build-deps so that bytestring has unconditional appearance
Tests: compatibility with newer bytestring with instance Show Builder

Fix #23: GHC-9.2 compilation failure due to change in ghc-prim

The type of `uncheckedShiftRL#` changed in ghc-prim-0.8.0.

The fix is taken from the GHC testsuite, see:

  https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/blob/100ffe75f509a73f1b26e768237888646f522b6c/testsuite/tests/profiling/should_run/T3001-2.hs#L159-160

To get the `MIN_VERSION_ghc_prim` macro, `ghc-prim` needs to be added
to the explicit dependencies in the cabal file.
